Government decided on Tuesday evening to temporarily halt the use of the vaccine. That after the United States put a pause to its J&J rollout after six people reported rare blood clots. eNCA’s Heidi Giokos has more. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Health Minister Zweli Mkhize says Pfizer has committed to supply batches of vaccines weekly. He says the first is expected to arrive on 3 May. READ: No-refund clauses in J&J and Pfizer vaccine agreements: Mkhize At least 15 million people will receive two Pfizer jabs. This as South Africa has suspended its Johnson & Johnson vaccine rollout. Six people in the United States reported rare blood clots.